Sentencas: A power generation system consisting of an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) and an external reformer for biogas is developed, and its performance is investigated for advanced use of effective biogas.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell employing reformed effective biogas: Power generation and inhibition of carbon deposition

Sentencas: The IT-SOFC is fueled with syngas produced via biogas reforming, and is successfully operated at 600 and 700 degrees C using Ni0.8Cu0.2 alloy/gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte (Ni0.8Cu0.2/GDC) cermet anodes and a LaAlO3 supported-Ni (Ni/LaAlO3) catalyst.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell employing reformed effective biogas: Power generation and inhibition of carbon deposition

Sentencas: The Ni/LaAlO3 catalyst stably exhibits high reforming performance for effective biogas at 800 degrees C for 27 h, and carbon deposition on the catalyst is prevented.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell employing reformed effective biogas: Power generation and inhibition of carbon deposition

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the Ni0.8Cu0.2/GDC cermet anode using syngas fuel possessing a H-2:CO ratio of approximately 3:1 is comparable to the performance achieved with H-2 fuel; the anode remains stable after 24 h of operation at 700 degrees C without interruption and is unaffected by carbon deposition.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell employing reformed effective biogas: Power generation and inhibition of carbon deposition
